trans-unit.source: Care must also be exercised when using collections that have restrictions on the elements that they may contain. trans-unit.source: Care must be exercised if this method is used on collections that do not comply with the general contract for Collection. Implementations may elect to iterate over either collection and test for containment in the other collection (or to perform any equivalent computation). If either collection uses a nonstandard equality test (as does a SortedSet whose ordering is not compatible with equals, or the key set of an IdentityHashMap), both collections must use the same nonstandard equality test, or the result of this method is undefined.

trans-unit.source: Care should be taken before granting code permission to access certain system properties. trans-unit.source: Care should be taken to ensure that a connected datagram socket is not shared with untrusted code. When a socket is connected, receive and sendwill not perform any security checks on incoming and outgoing packets, other than matching the packet's and the socket's address and port. On a send operation, if the packet's address is set and the packet's address and the socket's address do not match, an IllegalArgumentException will be thrown. A socket connected to a multicast address may only be used to send packets. Datagrams in the socket's socket receive buffer, which have not been received before invoking this method, may be discarded.
trans-unit.target: 应注意确保不与不受信任的代码共享连接的数据报套接字。连接套接字后， receive 和 send 将不会对传入和传出的数据包执行任何安全检查，除非匹配数据包的地址和套接字的地址和端口。在发送操作中，如果设置了数据包的地址，并且数据包的地址和套接字的地址不匹配，则将抛出 IllegalArgumentException 。连接到多播地址的套接字只能用于发送数据包。套接字的套接字接收缓冲区中的数据报（在调用此方法之前尚未被接收）可能会被丢弃。

trans-unit.source: Certain methods of this interface are considered "destructive" and are called "mutator" methods in that they modify the group of objects contained within the collection on which they operate. They can be specified to throw UnsupportedOperationException if this collection implementation does not support the operation. Such methods should (but are not required to) throw an UnsupportedOperationException if the invocation would have no effect on the collection. For example, consider a collection that does not support the add operation. What will happen if the addAll method is invoked on this collection, with an empty collection as the argument? The addition of zero elements has no effect, so it is permissible for this collection simply to do nothing and not to throw an exception. However, it is recommended that such cases throw an exception unconditionally, as throwing only in certain cases can lead to programming errors.

trans-unit.source: Channels of this type are safe for use by multiple concurrent threads though at most one accept operation can be outstanding at any time. If a thread initiates an accept operation before a previous accept operation has completed then an AcceptPendingException will be thrown.
trans-unit.target: 这种类型的通道可以安全地供多个并发线程使用，尽管最多可以随时执行一个接受操作。如果线程在上一个接受操作完成之前启动了接受操作，则将引发 AcceptPendingException 。

trans-unit.source: Channels of this type are safe for use by multiple concurrent threads. The close method may be invoked at any time, as specified by the Channel interface. This causes all outstanding asynchronous operations on the channel to complete with the exception AsynchronousCloseException. Multiple read and write operations may be outstanding at the same time. When multiple read and write operations are outstanding then the ordering of the I/O operations, and the order that the completion handlers are invoked, is not specified; they are not, in particular, guaranteed to execute in the order that the operations were initiated. The ByteBuffers used when reading or writing are not safe for use by multiple concurrent I/O operations. Furthermore, after an I/O operation is initiated then care should be taken to ensure that the buffer is not accessed until after the operation has completed.
trans-unit.target: 这种类型的通道可以安全地供多个并发线程使用。如 Channel 接口所指定的， close 方法可以随时调用。这将导致通道上所有未完成的异步操作完成，并带有 AsynchronousCloseException 异常。多个读取和写入操作可能同时处于未完成状态。当多个读和写操作尚未完成时，则不指定I / O操作的顺序以及完成处理程序的调用顺序。尤其不能保证它们以启动操作的顺序执行。该 ByteBuffers 在进行多个并发I / O操作不安全时进行读取或写入时使用。此外，在启动I / O操作之后，应注意确保直到操作完成后才访问缓冲区。

trans-unit.source: Channels of this type are safe for use by multiple concurrent threads. They support concurrent reading and writing, though at most one read operation and one write operation can be outstanding at any time. If a thread initiates a read operation before a previous read operation has completed then a ReadPendingException will be thrown. Similarly, an attempt to initiate a write operation before a previous write has completed will throw a WritePendingException.
trans-unit.target: 这种类型的通道可以安全地供多个并发线程使用。它们支持并发读取和写入，尽管最多可以随时执行一次读取操作和一个写入操作。如果线程在上一个读取操作完成之前启动了读取操作，则将引发 ReadPendingException 。类似地，尝试在上一次写入完成之前启动写入操作将抛出 WritePendingException 。

trans-unit.source: Character boundary analysis allows users to interact with characters as they expect to, for example, when moving the cursor through a text string. Character boundary analysis provides correct navigation through character strings, regardless of how the character is stored. The boundaries returned may be those of supplementary characters, combining character sequences, or ligature clusters. For example, an accented character might be stored as a base character and a diacritical mark. What users consider to be a character can differ between languages.
trans-unit.target: 字符边界分析允许用户按照他们所期望的方式与字符进行交互,例如,在文本字符串中移动光标时。字符边界分析提供了正确的字符串导航,无论字符是如何存储的。返回的边界可能是补充字符、组合字符序列或连接簇的边界。例如,一个重音字符可能被存储为一个基本字符和一个重音符号。用户认为什么是字符,在不同的语言中可能有所不同。

trans-unit.source: Checked exception received by a thread when a timeout elapses before an asynchronous operation completes.

trans-unit.source: Checked exception received by a thread when another thread closes the channel or the part of the channel upon which it is blocked in an I/O operation.
trans-unit.target: 当另一个线程在I/O操作中关闭通道或通道上被阻塞的部分时,线程收到的检查异常。

trans-unit.source: Checked exception received by a thread when another thread interrupts it while it is blocked in an I/O operation upon a channel.
trans-unit.target: 当一个线程在通道的I/O操作中被阻塞时,另一个线程中断它时,它收到的检查异常。

trans-unit.source: Checked exception received by a thread when another thread interrupts it while it is blocked in an I/O operation upon a channel. Before this exception is thrown the channel will have been closed and the interrupt status of the previously-blocked thread will have been set.
trans-unit.target: 当一个线程在通道的I/O操作中被阻塞时,另一个线程中断它时收到的检查异常。在该异常发生之前,通道已经被关闭,之前被阻塞的线程的中断状态已经被设置。

trans-unit.source: Checked exception received by a thread when another thread interrupts it while it is waiting to acquire a file lock.
trans-unit.target: 当一个线程在等待获取文件锁时,另一个线程中断它时,它收到的检查异常。

trans-unit.source: Checked exception received by a thread when another thread interrupts it while it is waiting to acquire a file lock. Before this exception is thrown the interrupt status of the previously-blocked thread will have been set.
trans-unit.target: 当一个线程在等待获取文件锁时,另一个线程中断它时,它收到的检查异常。在抛出该异常之前,之前被阻塞的线程的中断状态将被设置。

trans-unit.source: Checked exception thrown when a character encoding or decoding error occurs.

trans-unit.source: Checked exception thrown when an attempt is made to invoke or complete an I/O operation upon channel that is closed, or at least closed to that operation.
trans-unit.target: 当试图在关闭的通道上调用或完成I/O操作时,或至少对该操作关闭时,抛出检查异常。

trans-unit.source: Checked exception thrown when an attempt is made to invoke or complete an I/O operation upon channel that is closed, or at least closed to that operation. That this exception is thrown does not necessarily imply that the channel is completely closed. A socket channel whose write half has been shut down, for example, may still be open for reading.
trans-unit.target: 当试图调用或完成对通道的I/O操作,而通道是关闭的,或至少对该操作是关闭的时,抛出的检查异常。抛出这个异常并不一定意味着通道完全关闭。例如,一个写一半的socket通道已经被关闭,但仍然可以打开读取。

trans-unit.source: Checked exception thrown when an input byte sequence is not legal for given charset, or an input character sequence is not a legal sixteen-bit Unicode sequence.
trans-unit.target: 当输入的字节序列对给定的字符集不合法,或者输入的字符序列不是合法的16位Unicode序列时,抛出检查异常。

trans-unit.source: Checked exception thrown when an input character (or byte) sequence is valid but cannot be mapped to an output byte (or character) sequence.
trans-unit.target: 当输入字符(或字节)序列有效但不能映射到输出字节(或字符)序列时,抛出检查异常。
